HEADWORD: Double-milled
<hw>Dou"ble-milled`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Twice milled
or fulled, to render more compact or fine; -- said of cloth; <as>as,
<ex>double-milled</ex> kerseymere</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

